title: kagutsuchi_(mythology)
body: Kagutsuchi-no-Mikoto (軻遇突智命), also known by other names like Homusubi (火産霊), was the [[Japanese mythology| Japanese]] god of fire who his mother [[Izanami no Mikoto|]] died giving birth to. [[Izanagi no Mikoto | Izanagi]] was so heartbroken by her death that he took out his sword and killed the newborn Kagutsuchi, dismembering him. From Kagutsuchi's remains and blood respectively, several mountains and deities were born.

title: nohara_misae
body: Character from [[Crayon shin-chan]], Misae Nohara (野原 - みさえ), is the mother of the Nohara family and its caretaker. She is 29 years old but she always tells people that she is 24 or 25. She is the classical housewife (専業主婦 Sengyō shufu) of post-war Japan - she cleans, launders, cooks, sews, mothers and lazes all to varying degrees of success. Her maiden name is Misae Koyama (小山 - みさえ).

title: mera_jin
body:
Mera Jin (米良 仁), known to SNK fans as Shiroi Eiji (白井影二), is a freelancer, comic book artist, and dessin drawing teacher who was previously hired by [[SNK]] near the end of October in 1992. Her alias originated from the alternate palette swap of [[Kisaragi Eiji]] from [[Ryuuko no Ken|Art of Fighting 2]] (one of her favorite games at SNK). She is best known for being the main illustrator and character designer for the [[Samurai Spirits]] series. 
Her art while working at SNK were stylized ink paintings, made with dynamic brush strokes and characters posed with a subtle flow of motion. She is a lover of American comics (especially [[X-Men]]) and 1/6 scale miniature crafts.

h4. External links
* "SNK Wiki: Shiroi Eiji":https://snk.fandom.com/wiki/Shiroi_Eiji

He is a [[wolf boy]] wearing a [[white shirt|white]] [[collared shirt]], [[black vest]], and [[mask on head]]. He has [[medium hair]] tied into a [[low ponytail]]. His animal form is a black [[wolf]].

title: miss_fortune_(league_of_legends)
body:
A human Champion from Bilgewater in [[League of Legends]] usually played as an AD carry. She is known for her flirtatious and confident attitude, as well as her pirate-like attire (despite being a pirate [i]hunter[/i]) and [[dual wielding|dual-wielded]] [[gun|guns]] "Shock" and "Awe". She has [[long_hair|long]] [[red hair]] and [[large breasts]].

Has a personal vendetta with the pirate [[Gangplank (league of legends)|]] after he murdered her family and left her for dead.

Full title: Sarah Fortune (Miss Fortune) the Bounty Hunter

title: terminator:_dark_fate
body: Terminator: Dark Fate is a 2019 American science fiction action film. It is the sixth installment in the Terminator franchise and serves as a direct sequel to both [[The Terminator]] (1984) and [[Terminator 2: Judgment Day]] (1991), ignoring the events depicted in Rise of the Machines (2003), Terminator Salvation (2009), and [[Terminator Genisys]] (2015). The film stars Linda Hamilton and [[Arnold Schwarzenegger]] reprising their characters Sarah Connor and the [[T-800]] Terminator, respectively, and introduces Mackenzie Davis, Natalia Reyes, Gabriel Luna and Diego Boneta as new characters. Dark Fate is directed by Tim Miller and written by David S. Goyer, Justin Rhodes, and Billy Ray, based on a story by James Cameron, Charles H. Eglee, Josh Friedman, Goyer, and Rhodes.

title: mall_link_suit
body:
The [[mecha pilot suit]] worn by [[Kyouno Madoka]], [[Fin E Ld Si Laffinty]], and [[Muginami]] when piloting the Vox Units in [[Rinne no Lagrange]].

The suit consists is basically a [[bodysuit]] with a [[skirt]] on it. It contains [[see-through clothes|see-through]] parts on the back, shoulders, and upper part. These see-through parts become invisible when inside the Vox, giving the impression that the suit is actually a [[halterneck]] [[backless dress]] with [[detached sleeves]] and [[thigh boots]]. The inside Vox design is the one most used in illustrations, and as such posts are usually tagged corresponding with this design.

Additionally, the suits are individually designed the following:

* Madoka wears a [[green dress]] with no cutout.
* Lan (Laffinty) wears a [[blue dress]] with a [[side cutout]] on each side and an [[ass cutout]].
* Muginami wears an [[orange dress]] with a [[navel cutout]].

The upper borders of the "[[detached sleeves]]" and "[[thigh boots]]" of the suit also have a stripe of the suit's respective color.

title: miyatake_kazutaka
body:
[b]Miyatake Kazutaka[/b] (宮武 一貴) (Born September 21, 1949) is a japanese anime designer known for the mechanical design of the [[MACROSS]] series and a number of its continuations from Studio Nue. He has also contributed to the mecha design of other series such as [[Uchuu Senkan Yamato]], [[Techno Police 21C]], [[Ulysses 31]], [[Crusher Joe]], [[Orguss]], [[Seisenshi Dunbine]], [[Gunbuster]], [[RahXephon]], [[Sousei no Aquarion]] and [i]Mobile Suit [[Gundam SEED Destiny]][/i]. 

Miyatake also designed the [[power suit]]s in the 1988 OVA [[Uchuu No Senshi]], which he originally created for the Japanese edition of the novel [[Starship Troopers]] in the early 80s.

A humble genius, Miyatake Kazutaka seems to be the most easily overlooked man in [[mecha]] design despite being a prolific artist. He has displayed a versatile style and attention to detail that is impressive to behold. Miyatake has been described many times as the silent backbone of Studio Nue.

h4. Notable Designs: 
*  [[Yamato (Uchuu Senkan Yamato)]] (spacecraft)
*  [[SDF-1]] [i]Macross[/i] (mecha)
*  [[Orguss (mecha)]]
*  [[Dunbine]] (mecha)
*  [[Gunbuster (robot)]]
*  [[Uchuu No Senshi]] ([[power armor]]s)
*  [[YF-21]] Omega One ([[cockpit]], [[mecha pilot suit]])

h4. See also
* [[Miyatake Kazutaka (style)]]

She has [[long hair|long]] [[brown hair]] with [[swept bangs]].

title: mega_man_1
body:
[b]Rockman[/b], known as [b]Mega Man[/b] outside of Japan, is a 1987 2D action-platform [[video game]] developed and published by [[Capcom]] for the [[Nintendo]] [[Famicom]]/Nintendo Entertainment System (NES). 

It was directed by Kitamura Akira, with Matsushima Nobuyuki as lead programmer, and is the first game of the Mega Man franchise and the original video game series. Mega Man was produced by a small team specifically for the home [[game console]] market, a first for Capcom, who previously focused on [[arcade]] titles.

The game begins the struggle of the [[android]] and player-character [[Mega Man (character)|]] against the mad scientist [[Dr. Wily (mega man)|]] and the six "Robot Masters" under his control. Mega Man's nonlinear gameplay lets the player choose the order in which to complete its initial six stages. Each culminates in a boss battle against one of the Robot Masters that awards the player-character a unique weapon. Part of the strategy of the game is that the player must carefully choose the order in which to tackle the stages so that they can earn the weapons that will be most useful for future stages.

Critics praised Mega Man for its overall design, though the game was not a commercial success. Mega Man established many of the gameplay, story, and graphical conventions that would define the ensuing sequels, subseries, and spin-offs in the [[Mega Man (classic)|]] franchise. 

The first game has since been featured in game compilations, including Mega Man Legacy Collection for Windows, [[PlayStation 4]], [[Xbox One]], [[Nintendo 3DS]], and [[Nintendo Switch]], rereleased on mobile phones, and become a part of console emulation services. It received a full 3D remake titled [[Mega Man: Powered Up]] in 2006.

h6. Robot Masters

* [[Cut Man]]
* [[Guts Man]]
* [[Ice Man]]
* [[Bomb Man]]
* [[Fire Man]]
* [[Elec Man]]

h6. Fortress Bosses

title: loitering_munition
body:
A loitering munition, also known as a [[suicide]] [[drone]], is a kind of aerial [[weapon]] with a built-in [[explosive|warhead]] that is typically designed to loiter around a target area until a target is located, then attack the target by crashing into it. Loitering munitions enable faster reaction times against hidden targets that emerge for short periods without placing high-value platforms near the target area and also allow more selective targeting as the attack can be changed mid-flight or aborted.

h4. External links: 
https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Loitering_munition

title: terminator_genisys
body: Terminator Genisys is a 2015 American cyberpunk action film that is the fifth installment in [[the Terminator]] franchise. It is a reboot of the franchise, taking the premise of the original film in another direction and ignoring the events depicted in sequels and the TV series.
other_names: ターミネーター:新起動/ジェニシス

title: terminator_3:_rise_of_the_machines
body: Terminator 3: Rise of the Machines[a] is a 2003 science fiction action film, the third installment in [[the Terminator]] franchise and a sequel to [[Terminator 2: Judgment Day]] (1991). It is directed by Jonathan Mostow and stars [[Arnold Schwarzenegger]], Nick Stahl, Claire Danes, and Kristanna Loken. In its plot, the malevolent artificial intelligence Skynet sends a T-X (Loken)—a highly advanced Terminator—back in time to ensure the rise of machines by killing top members of the future human resistance as John Connor's (Stahl) location is unknown. The resistance sends back a reprogrammed T-850 (Schwarzenegger) to protect John and Kate (Danes).

title: terminator_(series)
body:
A media franchise originating from an American science fiction film series about a post-apocalyptic war between an artificial intelligence called Skynet and the survivors of the human race. Both sides use time travel in an attempt to stop or win the war before it happens. Major stars in one or more films in the series include [[Arnold Schwarzenegger]] as the titular Terminator (an antagonist in the first film but a protagonist after) and Linda Hamilton and Emilia Clarke as Sarah Connor.

Six movies have been produced: [[The Terminator]] (1984), [[Terminator 2: Judgment Day]] (1991), [[Terminator 3: Rise of the Machines]] (2003), Terminator Salvation (2009), [[Terminator Genisys]] (2015), and [[Terminator: Dark Fate]] (2019). Also, a TV series based on the same universe called [[Terminator: The Sarah Connor Chronicles]] was released in 2008.

He is often seen in a [[black jacket]] and [[black cloak]]. His signature trait is his [[red hair|red]] [[colored tips]], and he’s associated with [[fire]].

title: kaiba_seto
body:
[[Yu-Gi-Oh!]] character. [[Muto Yugi]]'s biggest rival and largely believed to be the anti-hero of [[Yu-Gi-Oh! Duel Monsters]]. 

He and his younger brother [[Kaiba Mokuba]] were adopted from an orphanage by Gozaburo Kaiba. Arrogant and power-driven, he believes that he is the best duelist in the world. Seto took over his stepfather's company Kaiba Corporation at a young age and became the president of Kaiba Corp, turning it from a major arms dealer to the biggest gaming company in the world of [[Yu-Gi-Oh!]] and among the most influential in the United States.

His signature monster is the [[Blue-Eyes White Dragon]]. He is obsessed with it to the point where he includes his motif on everything he owns.

h4. See also
* [[Priest Seto]] - Kaiba's ancient Egyptian incarnation
* [[Kaiba's defeat (meme)]]

title: jesse_pinkman
body:
Deuteragonist of the American crime drama television series [[Breaking Bad]]. Jesse partners with his former high school chemistry teacher [[Walter White]] to cook and sell methamphetamine.

Seen early in the series with a [[beanie]] obscuring [[short hair|short]], [[brown hair]]. Also frequently wearing a [[hoodie]] and any number of graphic [[shirt|shirts]].

Later in the series, he shaves his head and takes on a less eccentric wardrobe, largely ditching his beanies as well.

He was portrayed by Aaron Paul. Jesse is the only character besides Walter to appear in every episode of the show. Paul reprised the role for the 2019 spin-off sequel film El Camino: A Breaking Bad Movie, set after its finale, and again in 2022 for the sixth and final season of the spin-off prequel sequel series [[Better Call Saul]], being one of the few characters to appear across both shows and the movie.

title: needle_knight_leda
body:
[b]Needle Knight Leda[/b], is a character in [[Elden Ring: Shadow of the Erdtree]]. She is a follower of [[miquella_(elden_ring)|Miquella]], and the character you meet in order to access the expansion.
While she never removes her helmet in-game, "official artwork of her":[/posts/7619575] without her helmet was released, showing she has [[blonde hair]] tied with a [[braid]]. Her face has since been compared to [[Saber_(fate)|]] from the [[fate_(series)|Fate franchise]].

[spoilers]Despite the cordial and friendly impressions she initially gives, it is revealed to be a facade once Miquella's charm is broken. Beneath her image of an ideal knight, she is highly zealous and viciously paranoid, eager to hunt her fellow seekers on the suspicion of disloyalty to Miquella.[/spoilers]

title: ramesseum_tentyris
body:
[b]The Shining Great Temple Complex[/b]

A [[noble phantasm (fate)|]] possessed by [[Ozymandias (fate)|]]. It consists of several different temple complexes linked together, with the [[pyramid (structure)|]] Ramesseum serving as its center.

Featured in [[Fate/Grand Order]] by him trapping enemies by having two pyramids with the [[Eye of Horus]] on them slam together around enemies, meeting at the point.

Crashes onto [[Elizabeth Bathory (fate)|]]'s Csejte Castle in [[Halloween Comeback!]], and has [[Himeji Castle]] land on top of it in [[Halloween Strike!]], creating the [[Csejte Pyramid Himeji Castle]].

title: sword_maiden
body:
One of the main characters from [[Goblin Slayer!]]. She is a priestess with proficient swordsmanship.

[spoiler]Formerly known as [[Female Bishop (goblin slayer!)|]]. In her past, she was captured by goblins who violated and tortured her. She was left permanently blinded and traumatically afraid of goblins. She eventually went on to join the party of heroes who slew the demon lord, as covered in the events of [[Goblin Slayer Side Story II: Daikatana]]. [/spoiler]

title: goblin_slayer!
body:
2016 Dark Fantasy light novel and manga, written by Kumo Kagyu and illustrated by [[Kannatsuki Noboru]]. An anime adaptation aired in October 2018.

The story follows the journey of the titular character known as [[Goblin Slayer]], an adventurer who hunts [[goblin]]s and only goblins. 

The anime adaptation also became controversial in the West after the airing of the first episode for retaining the extreme violence (including [[rape]] scenes) from the light novel not helped by at least one streaming site not properly labeling the series for said content.

title: knitting_needle
body: A large-sized [[needle]] that isn't sharp at the pointed end. Two are used in conjunction for the art of [[knitting]] by stitching yarn together to weave a piece of cloth. Knitting needles are sometimes erroniously depicted with a hook on the end similar to [[crochet hook]]s, but are distinct in that they have a constant thickness over their shaft, and don’t narrow right before the tip.

body:
A 1997 romantic disaster movie directed, written, co-produced and co-edited by [[James Cameron]] about a fictional couple from different social classes who fell in love on board the [[RMS Titanic]] during its ill-fated voyage in 1912. Although based on real events surrounding the sinking, the story is fictionalized, focusing on said couple and people related to them, rather than the sinking itself.

title: shulker
body:
Light purple, box-shaped hostile mob in [[Minecraft]]. Only spawns in End Cities located in [[The End (Minecraft)|]] dimension. It fires specialized bullets that can cause an entity to experience [[levitation]] for a few seconds. Similar to the [[ghast]] [[fireball]], players can deflect that projectile. Has a [[teleportation]] ability. 

Once the shulker completely closes its shell, it becomes almost invulnerable to damage and can deflect [[arrow (projectile)|]]s.

Shulkers have chance to drop their own [[shulker shell|shell(s)]], vital components to craft [[shulker box]]es.

h4. See also

* [[List of Minecraft characters]]

title: katsuragi_misato
body:
A character from [[Neon Genesis Evangelion]] who is the chief operations officer at [[Nerv]]. She is the field commander for the [[Ayanami Rei|Eva pilots]] and guardian of [[Ikari Shinji]] and [[Souryuu Asuka Langley]] who stay at her home.

[spoiler]Misato and her father were involved in the Second Impact as he was a top scientist who in the last moment put Misato in a escape capsule so she could survive the event. Afterwards Misato became [[crazy]] with survivor guilt and was admitted into a mental institution for most of her teenage years. After being released in her adult years she developed a very extroverted and cheerful personality to be able to cope with her past tragedies.[/spoiler]

Misato has a pet [[mutant]] [[penguin]] named [[PenPen]]; and she was the lover of [[Kaji Ryouji]].

title: gardenia_(pokemon)
body:
[b]Gardenia[/b], known as [b]Natane[/b] (ナタネ) in Japan, is a character introduced in [i][[pokemon dppt|Pokémon Diamond and Pearl]][/i].

This bold Gym Leader uses Grass-type Pokémon and is quite scared of ghosts and anything that surprises her. Her fear sometimes keeps her up at night [tn](official bio)[/tn]. Her signature Pokémon is [[Roserade]].

She has [[orange eyes]] and [[short hair|short]] [[orange hair|orange]] [[two-tone hair|and]] [[black hair]] with [[blunt bangs]]. She wears a [[poncho]] over a [[long sleeves|long-sleeve]] [[black shirt]] which is [[cropped shirt|cropped]] and bares her [[midriff]], [[torn shorts|torn]] [[cargo shorts]], a [[black belt]], and [[green footwear|green]] [[boots]].

body:

This passionate Gym Leader has a fixation on focus. However, she sometimes wonders if she should play it cooler as an Ice-type Pokémon user [tn](official bio)[/tn]. Her signature Pokémon is [[Abomasnow]].

She has [[brown eyes]] and [[long hair|long]] [[black hair]] [[multi-tied hair|tied]] into [[twintails]]. title: soulcalibur
body:
A fighting game series published by [[Namco]]. Compared to its sister series [[Tekken]], the series focuses on weapons combat and features more freeform 3D movement - a mechanic referred to as the "8-Way Run". The setting takes place in the late 16th and early 17th century and focuses primarily on the tales surrounding two legendary weapons, the eponymous [[Soul Edge (weapon)|Soul Edge]] and [[Soul Calibur (weapon)|Soul Calibur]]; the former is a corruptive weapon born of death that seeks to reap souls for power, while the latter is the diametric opposite and aims to destroy or otherwise stop its sibling.

title: irida_(pokemon)
body:
[b]Irida (English) / Kai (Japanese)[/b] is a character introduced in [i][[pokemon legends: arceus|Pokémon Legends: Arceus]][/i].

Irida serves as the leader of the Pearl Clan, and her partner Pokémon is [[Glaceon]].

As a leader, she feels it is important to have the courage to face the vast Hisui region without quailing before it. Though she is suspicious of you when you first meet, she will come to trust you thanks to the help you provide in quelling the noble Pokémon.

title: amano_nene_(vtuber)_(goddess)
body:
The 5th [[official alternate costume|costume]] of [[production kawaii]]'s [[Amano Nene (vtuber)|]], as seen in post #6409202.

It's a goddess-themed costume consisting of a gold [[circlet]] a [[white hood]], a gold [[neck ring]] a criss-cross a [[white bikini|white]] [[sling bikini top]] with [[gold chain]]s, [[white sleeves|white]] [[see-through sleeves|see-through]] [[detached sleeves]] gold [[bracelet]]s, a frilled [[underbust]] half leotard with a [[navel cutout]], [[white garter straps]], a [[white skirt|white]] [[see-through skirt|see-through]] [[high-low skirt|high-low]] [[showgirl skirt]] and wite [[leg ribbon]]'s giving the impression of [[barefoot sandals (jewelry)|]].

Her [[official alternate hairstyle|official hairstyle]] with this costume is a [[single braid|single]] [[side braid]] [[hair over shoulder|over her shoulders]] decorated with small [[hair flower|flowers]] and the [[wing hair ornament|wing-shaped]] [[hairclip]] from her nun costume.

body:
The 4th [[official alternate costume|costume]] of [[production kawaii]]'s [[Amano Nene (vtuber)|]], as seen in post #6335381 and post #6082258. It's her official [[idol]] ouftif and her first 3D outfit, sharing a similar design theme with the other [[production kawaii|kawaii]] members idol outfits. It was designed by [[hane yuki]].

It consist of a [[high collar|high-collared]] [[cropped vest|cropped]] [[blue vest]] with a [[framed breasts|breast frame]] and [[fake wings]] on the back, an [[arm garter]], [[white gloves]], a [[blue skirt|blue]] [[miniskirt]] with a [[see-through skirt|see-through hemline]] and a [[large bow|large]] [[back bow]], [[mismatched legwear|mismatched]] [[white thighhighs|white]] and [[blue thighhighs]] and [[blue footwear|blue]] [[high heel boots]].

Her hairstyle with this outfit is largely the same as her first outfit with the addition of [[pom pom hair ornament]]s and [[x hair ornament|crossed]] [[hairclip]]s on one side and a [[winged heart]] one on the other.

title: amano_nene_(vtuber)_(casual)
body:
The 3rd [[official alternate costume|costume]] of [[production kawaii]]'s [[Amano Nene (vtuber)|]], as seen in post #6409181.

It consist of a either a [[crop top|cropped]] [[pink shirt|pink]] or [[grey shirt|frey]] [[frilled shirt|frilled]] [[off-shoulder shirt]] with [[spaghetti strap]]s or a pink [[sleeveless turtleneck]] [[sleeveless shirt]] with a [[heart cutout|heart]] [[cleavage cutout]] reminiscing of her 1st outfit, [[black shorts]] with [[black panties|black]] [[highleg panties]] [[panty straps|peeking out]], [[white socks]] and [[red footwear|red]] [[mary janes]]. She also has an optional [[pink jacket|pink]] or [[aqua jacket|aqua]] [[hooded jacket]] with [[cross-laced sleeves]].

Her [[official alternate hairstyle|official hairstyle]] with this outfit is a [[ponytail]] with a [[wing hair ornament|wing-shaped]] [[hair bow]]. She can also mix and match with the hairstyles from her previous outfits.

title: amano_nene_(vtuber)_(nun)
body:
The 2nd [[official alternate costume|costume]] of [[production kawaii]]'s [[Amano nene (vtuber)|]], as seen in post #5309473 and post #5092020.

It's a non-traditional [[nun]] habit consisting of a [[black veil]] a white [[detached collar|detached]] [[high collar]], a [[long dress|long]] [[strapless dress|strapless]] [[black dress|black]] [[impossible dress]] with [[side slit]]s forming a [[pelvic curtain]], [[black sleeves|black]] [[detached sleeves|detached]] [[juliet sleeves]] with [[sleeve garter]]s and [[sleeve cuffs]], [[white thighhighs]] held with [[legwear garter]]s and [[blue footwear|black]] [[pumps]].

Her [[official alternate hairstyle|official hairstyle]] with this outfit is [[medium hair]] tied into [[low twintails]] or [[long hair]] tied into regular [[twintails]] with [[sidelocks]] and a small [[wing hair ornament|wing-shaped]] [[hairclip]].

title: imca
body:
Character in [[Senjou no Valkyria 3]].

Imca (イムカ Imuka), also known as "Ace" or "Number 1," is a [[black hair|Darcsen]] heavy weapon specialist whose village was destroyed by the Valkyria and she is seeking revenge. No matter what the situation she always uses her prized weapon, [[var (senjou no valkyria)|Var]], which can be outfitted to suit all infantry classes. She is voiced by [[Asano Masumi]].

title: star_wars:_republic_commando
body:
A first-person shooter game in the [[Star Wars]] series, first released for [[Xbox (original)|]] and [[computer|PC]] in 2005. The game has players take command of Delta Squad, a team of elite [[Clone Trooper]]s, and allows the player to give their squadmates orders. 

A series of 5 novels and several short stories and comics based on the game's characters were released, with the first book released several months ahead of the game in 2004. A sequel to the game was planned, but was canceled in the concept art phase. This sequel would've been titled [b]Star Wars: Imperial Commando[/b], and the title was reused for the final book in the novel series.

Despite the original game and books being removed from canon after [[Disney]]'s acquisition of the franchise, Delta Squad made a canon cameo appearance in [[Star Wars: The Clone Wars]], and the concept of Clone Commandos has remained in the franchise through [[star wars: The Bad Batch|The Bad Batch]] and the playable Clone Commando class in [[Electronic Arts]]' Battlefront II.

h4. Characters

* [[Boss (star wars)|]]
* [[Fixer (star wars)|]]
* [[Scorch (star wars)|]]
* [[Sev (star wars)|]]

title: j_(reverse:1999)
body:
[b]J[/b], or [b]Joe[/b], is a playable character in [[Reverse:1999]]. Leader of his biker gang in Haight Street, helping the unfortunate and protecting them. He is one of the main protagonist in the event "Floor It! To the Golden City", where he and his gang helped drive away a cult from their town. He has a bike and a big sword wrapped in white cloth, always hanging on his back. He is friends with [[Mercuria (Reverse:1999)|Mercuria]] and [[Pioneer (Reverse:1999)|Pioneer]].

title: sword_of_kusanagi
body:
A sword which is currently in the Japanese royal Regalia, supposedly from mythical times. It is often depicted as a [[katana]] in fiction, however the most reliable images show it as a older form of short sword.

In the [[Touhou]] fandom, [[Morichika Rinnosuke]] is believed to have it in his antique shop and some artists depict it as his weapon of choice. Canon only states that it was discovered in [[Kirisame Marisa]]'s hoard and was renamed "Sword of Kirisame" "(霧雨の剣)":http://dic.pixiv.net/a/%E9%9C%A7%E9%9B%A8%E3%81%AE%E5%89%A3 in [[Curiosities of Lotus Asia]]. 

In [[The King of Fighters]] series, the main character [[Kusanagi Kyou|Kusanagi Kyo]] holds the weapon inside his body, so as to make him be able to wield flames and seal Orochi.

In the [[Len'en]] series, [[Adagumo no Yaorochi]] was born from Orochi's severed arm and because of this, [[androgynous|he/she]] has a connection with the sword, whose real name is [[Tasouken]] (蛇叢剣).

h4.See also

* "Wikipedia article":http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Kusanagi
* [[Kusanagi no Tsurugi (Fate)]]

title: i-26_(azur_lane)
body:
[[Azur Lane]]'s personification of the Japanese submarine I-26.

In real life, she was the submarine responsible for the sinking of [[Juneau (Azur Lane)|]] in the naval battle of Guadalcanal, and before that, torpedoed [[Saratoga (Azur Lane)|]] shortly after the battle of the Eastern Solomons. Despite being the third-highest scoring IJN submarine in terms of tonnage sunk, she disappared without a trace on October 1944.

title: houston_(azur_lane)
body:
[[Azur Lane]]'s depiction of USS Houston (CL/CA-30), which was a Northampton-class cruiser of the United States Navy. She was the second Navy ship to bear the name "Houston". She was launched from Newport News, Virginia on 7 September 1929 and was sunk by torpedos in the Battle of Sunda Strait, on 1 March 1942.

title: gummy_(arknights)
body:
[i]Gummy, Defender Operator of Rhodes Island, will heal her teammates while protecting them[/i]

A playable Defender Operator in [[Arknights]].

Real Name: [spoiler]Lada[/spoiler]

h4. Profile
[expand]
[table]
[tbody]
      [tr][td]Place of Birth:[/td]
      [td]Ursus[/td][/tr]
      [tr][td]Birthday:[/td]
      [td]October 2[/td][/tr]
      [tr][td]Race:[/td]
      [td]Ursus[/td][/tr]
      [tr][td]Height:[/td]
      [td]155 cm[/td][/tr]
      [tr][td]Combat Experience:[/td]
      [td]None[/td][/tr]
  [/tbody]
[/table]
[/expand]

A member of Ursus Student Self-Governing Group along with [[Zima (Arknights)|]] and [[Istina (Arknights)|]]. She and her group took refuge at Rhodes Island during the fall of Chernobog at the end of Episode One. A lively, kind, and pure girl. She always speaks from the heart and has a genuine desire to please everyone. In battle, she uses a frying pan as her weapon of choice and a vault door as her shield.

She is one of the protagonists of the side story event [i]Children of Ursus[/i].

Her motif is based on sun bears.

Her [[voice actor]]s are [[Takamori Natsumi]] (Japanese), Liang Ruixue (Chinese), Cristina Vee (English), Kim Chae-ha (Korean), and Varvara Sarantseva (Russian). Her illustrator is [[Skade]].

title: hood_(azur_lane)
body:
[i][[Azur Lane]][/i]'s personification of the battlecruiser HMS [i]Hood[/i]. 
Character design by [[Sa (h28085)|]], voiced by [[Tanaka Atsuko]].

She has [[blue eyes]] and [[long hair|long]] [[blonde hair]] worn [[hair over shoulder|over one shoulder]]. She is depicted as an elegant lady dressed in Edwardian fashion, wearing a [[medium dress|medium]] [[blue dress]], a [[capelet]] with a [[Union Jack]] pattern, [[ascot]], and a [[white headwear|white]] [[tilted headwear|tilted]] [[hat]] with her real-life bridge. 

Her [[rigging]] consists of all four of her 381 mm twin gun mounts, two per side, with [[anti-aircraft gun]]s on the tops of the lower turrets.

body:
In the world of [[Avatar Legends]], the Avatar State is a power that can be activated by the Avatar, granting them the collective power of all their past incarnations.

An Avatar in this state will have [[glowing eyes]]. In the case of [[Aang]], his [[glowing tattoo|tattoos will also glow]] as they represent lines of chi flowing through the body.

title: roku_(avatar)
body:
A character from the [[Avatar Legends]] franchise.

He was one of the previous incarnations of the Avatar, a powerful being who can control all four elements. He was a [[pyrokineses|Firebender]] who succeeded Avatar [[Kyoshi (Avatar)|]] and preceded Avatar [[Aang]]. As the immediate predecessor to Aang, he made several appearances in [[Avatar: The Last Airbender|The Last Airbender]], acting as Aang's spiritual mentor.

He is an [[old man]] with [[long hair|long]] [[white hair]]. He wears a [[xiao guan (headdress)|]] and a [[red robe]] typical of the Fire Nation.

His animal guide was a dragon he named [[Fang (avatar)|]].

title: shoukaku_(azur_lane)
body:
[[Azur Lane]]'s personification of the Japanese aircraft carrier [i]Shoukaku[/i]. 
Character design by [[Enka (bcat)]], voiced by [[Taneda Risa]].

Her appearance is strikingly similar to [[Shoukaku (kancolle)|]] from [[Kantai Collection]], with the only major differences being her [[blue eyes]] and her [[white hair]] being done [[one side up]] while swapping out the hairband for a red spider lily. The sleeves to her outfit are elongated, however, meant to bear a resemblance to her namesake bird. 

While similar in ladylike design and apparently polite personality with her [[Shoukaku (kancolle)|Kancolle counterpart]], Azur Lane's Shoukaku is far more jaded and sarcastic, looking down upon her seniors and considering them fools for their failure at the Battle of Midway. In spite of her caustic attitude towards her "sempais", she does dote on her sister [[zuikaku_(azur_lane)|Zuikaku]] and the [[commander_(azur_lane)|Commander]].

title: ookami_mio_(hololive_summer_2019)
body:
The original [[bikini]] [[official alternate costume|costume]] of [[Ookami Mio]], first featured in the [i][[hololive]] Idol Project 2019 Summer[/i]. While initially not having a name, the swimsuit was given the name [i]Summer Vacation[/i] in the [i][[Azur Lane]][/i] collab on late 2019 as a limited-time skin.

It consist of a [[two-sided jacket|two-sided]] [[black jacket|black]] [[hooded jacket]] worn over a [[white bikini|white]] [[front-tie bikini top|front-tie]] [[bikini]] with a [[leaf print|leaf]] [[print bikini|print]] and a [[side-tie bikini bottom]], [[white shorts|white]] [[short shorts|shorts]] [[side slit shorts]], a black [[thigh strap]] and black [[high heels|high-heel]] [[sandals]].

Her [[official alternate hairstyle|official hairstyle]] with this swimsuit is [[very long hair]] tied into a [[wide ponytail]] with [[sidelocks]] and decorated with her usual eye glint [[hairclip]].

h4. Appearance

* !post #3648522: Profile

title: mermaid_(donkey_kong_64)
body:

She has [[long hair|long]] [[blonde hair]], [[blue eyes]] and sports [[large breasts]]. She wears [[blue eyeshadow]], a [[silver tiara]], a [[pendant]] and a blue [[shell_bikini|seashelled bikini]].  

Her character model is later reused in [i][[Banjo-Tooie]][/i] as decrepit statues in the Atlantis portion of Jolly Roger Lagoon

title: karen_(class_of_09)
body:
A character in [[class of 09|Class of '09]] and its sequels. 

A nerdy girl who enjoys reading and photography. Despite being ignorant to the various amoral topics covered in the visual novel, she is often seen as the most "normal" character in the cast due to her lack of negative traits.

title: lynn_hadley
body:
A character in [[class of 09|Class of '09]] and its sequels. 

She is the rather apathetic principal of the high school the visual novel is set in, as she cares very little for her students, as well as refusing to take action against the various immoral traits harbored within the faculty.

title: nicole's_mother_(class_of_09)
body:
A character in [[class of 09|Class of '09]] and its sequels. 

She is the mother of both [[Nicole (class of 09)|]] and Gamer Brother (nickname given by Nicole; his real name unknown).

title: kelly_(class_of_09)
body:
A character in [[class of 09|Class of '09]] and its sequels. 

Kelly is an extroverted and lively girl, who usually gets along with a majority of the cast, unless she is threatened or insulted. She works as the part-time manger of the FYE at the local mall, in which she takes her job very seriously, as seen in some routes.

title: bleach
body:
A very popular long running shounen manga and anime series by [[Kubo Tite]]. 

The story revolves around [[Kurosaki Ichigo]], a young man who became a [[shinigami]] after his encounter with [[Kuchiki Rukia]] and his adventure into the afterlife and beyond.

h4. Sagas

In roughly chronological order:

* [[Bleach: Turn Back the Pendulum|Turn Back the Pendulum]]
* [[Bleach: Memories of Nobody|Memories of Nobody]] (filler)
* [[Bleach: Zanpakutou Ibun Hen|Zanpakutou Ibun Hen]] (filler)
* [[bleach: sennen kessen-hen|The Thousand-Year Blood War]]
* [[Bleach: Epilogue|Epilogue]]

h4. Objects / Clothes / Symbols

body:

The Prefect Team is responsible for disciplinary actions and general policing of the Gehenna Academy student body, as well as being a functional army. Frequently clashes with the Pandemonium Society.

title: kuruk_(avatar)
body:
A character from the [[Avatar Legends]] franchise.

He was one of the previous incarnations of the Avatar, a powerful being who can control all four elements. He was a [[hydrokinesis|Waterbender]] who succeeded Avatar [[Yangchen (Avatar)|]] and preceded Avatar [[Kyoshi (Avatar)|]], [[Roku (Avatar)|]], and [[Aang]].

title: kyoshi_(avatar)
body:
A character from the [[Avatar Legends]] franchise.

She was one of the previous incarnations of the Avatar, a powerful being who can control all four elements. She was an [[geokinesis|Earthbender]]  who succeeded Avatar [[Kuruk (Avatar)|]] and preceded Avatar [[Roku (Avatar)|]] and [[Aang]].

She has [[long hair|long]], [[brown hair]] and wears [[makeup]] resembling the kind seen in [[Peking opera]]. She also wears a golden [[headdress]], a [[green kimono]], and often [[dual wielding|dual wields]] [[folding fan]]s. She was known to be very tall and very longlived, reaching the age of 230.

title: ozai
body:
The main antagonist in [[Avatar: The Last Airbender]]. He is the Fire Lord, the ruler of the Fire Nation whose goal is to conquer the other nations of the world.

He is the father to [[Zuko|Prince Zuko]] and brother of [[Iroh]]. He has [[yellow eyes]], [[long air|long]] [[black hair]] and a narrow [[beard]].

title: iroh
body:
A character in [[Avatar: The Last Airbender]]. He is the brother of Fire Lord [[Ozai]] and uncle of Prince [[Zuko]]. He accompanied Zuko during the latter's exile and quest to find the Avatar.

He is a fat, elderly man with [[grey hair|grey]] [[mutton chops]] and a [[beard]].

body:
A class of [[electric locomotive|Electric]] [[locomotive|locomotives]] formerly operating in Japan. 

[[Japan Railways|JNR]] [[Class EF63]] [[locomotive|locomotives]] were built between 1962 and 1976 exclusively for use as bankers (U.S. "helpers" or "pushers") on the steeply-graded Usui Pass section of the Shinetsu Main Line between Yokokawa and Karuizawa. They replaced the Class ED42 electric locomotives previously used on the rack-and-pinion line between these two stations.

title: jr_east_209_series
body:
The 209 series (209系) is an  [[multiple unit train|electric multiple unit]] ([[multiple unit train|EMU]]) [[train|commuter train]] type operated by [[East Japan Railway Company]] (JR East) in the Tokyo area of Japan since 1993.

The 209 series was the first of the "New series trains" (新系列電車, Shin-keiretsu densha), and served as the basis for the E501, E217, 701, and E127 series rolling stock, as well as the succeeding [[JR East E231 Series|E231 series]] stock. which in turn became the blueprint for successive trains developed by JR East and other railway companies in Japan.

title: qubeley_papillon
body: A [[mobile suit]] from [[Gundam Build Fighters]], the Qubeley Papillon is a custom [[Qubeley]] [[gunpla]] built by Nemesis and used by [[Aila Jyrkiainen]]. The unit is equipped with a [[lance]] bit, standard [[funnels (gundam)|]], clear [[funnels (gundam)|]] (made of clear plastic to create the illusion of invisible attacks), a [[energy sword]], a [[beam rifle]], and the [[shield]] nipper.

title: gundam_epyon
body:
[b]OZ-13MS Gundam Epyon[/b]
A Gundam-type [[Mobile Suit]] developed by [[Treize Khushrenada]] based on the [[Tallgeese]] and 5 Operation Meteor Gundams. True to Treize's philosophy of combat, it was only armed with melee weapons: a heat rod and a very high-output, large [[energy sword]] that is capable of destroying space fortresses. It also possessed the ability to transform into a flight mode (with a twin-headed dragon design), and was equipped with the fearsome [I]Epyon System[/I], a modified version of the ZERO System that enabled its pilot to control the battlefield. 

While it was originally [[Heero Yuy]] that relieved Treize of the Epyon, he later exchanges the unit for the [[Wing Gundam Zero]] with [[Zechs Merquise]] after a brief scuffle.

title: protagonist_(smtv)
body:
The player character from [[Shin Megami Tensei V]].

A male high school student who appears rather [[androgynous]]. He has an [[asymmetrical hair|asymmetrical]] [[bowl cut]] with icy [[blue eyes]] and sports a [[school uniform]] with [[floral print]]. Upon fusing with [[Aogami (megami tensei)|]], his appearance alters as he transforms into another being known as a [b]Nahobino[/b]. Here his hair becomes [[blue hair|dark blue]] and [[very long hair|very long]], while his eyes change to a [[yellow eyes|bright yellow color]]. Whether it is part of his body or an article of clothing isn't entirely clear, but it appears that the protagonist wears some sort of [[bodysuit]] in this form, and he can cause a [[energy sword]] to protrude from his fingertips at will.

title: fx_burst
body:
A special combat mode of the [[Gundam AGE-FX]], installed after its first deployment. Upon activation of the FX Burst Mode, the AGE-FX's limiters are disabled, maximizing its mobility at the cost of having decreased accuracy. It can wipe out large groups of enemy forces if used to its full potential.

When the FX Burst Mode is turned on, the AGE-FX turns blue and blue-colored [[energy sword|beam blades]] are emitted from ports all around the suit, including the [[funnels (gundam)|C-Funnels]]' storage points.

In Star Trek stories the devices are issued by the fictional Starfleet organization.

title: uss_enterprise_ncc-1701-a
body:
A fictional spacecraft from the [[Star Trek]] universe, and the primary setting for the fifth and sixth Star Trek films (it was seen briefly at the end of the fourth film).  Succeeded the [i]USS Enterprise[/i] NCC-1701 after that ship's destruction in Star Trek III: the Search For Spock, and was eventually replaced in-universe (after only 7 apparent years of service) by the [i]Enterprise[/i]-B.

No canon origin exists for the 1701-A.  A popular theory is that the ship was originally in service under another name (possibly [i]Yorktown[/i], per a comment supposedly made in passing by Gene Roddenberry himself after Star Trek IV had premiered) and was hurriedly renamed in the aftermath of the main events of Star Trek IV.  Some non-canon reference materials published in the 1980s speculated that the ship was a new build and was constructed for use as a testbed for the Transwarp drive project; Scotty's comments in Star Trek V about how the ship had numerous problems (and essentially broke down) on it's shakedown cruise would seem to support part of this theory.  Similarly, beyond being decommissioned after the events of Star Trek VI, the ship does not have a canon fate.  The non-canon novel The Ashes of Eden shows the ship being sold for use by the defense force of the planet Chal before being destroyed defending that world.

title: cranky_kong
body:
The elder of the Kong Family, introduced in [i][[Donkey Kong Country]][/i]. A grouchy, bitter old ape who constantly breaks the [[fourth wall]] to chastise [[Donkey Kong]] and reminisce about the good old days before the "newfangled graphics". 

While usually officially affirmed to being Donkey Kong's grandfather, some official sources claim he is the father instead. He is also the husband of Wrinkly Kong.

He has a [[very long beard|very long]] [[white beard]] and [[wrinkled_skin|wrinkled]] lips. He usually wears a [[brown sweater vest]], [[black-framed_eyewear|black]] [[glasses]] and typically holds a wooden walking [[cane]].

The Donkey Kong Country manual states that he was the ape that fought [[Mario]] and kidnapped [[Pauline (mario)|Pauline]] in the original [i][[Donkey Kong (1981 game)|Donkey Kong]][/i].

title: beverly_crusher
body: Beverly Crusher is a fictional character in the [[Star Trek]] franchise, played by Gates McFadden. Debuting in the television series [[Star Trek: The Next Generation]], McFadden appeared in every season except for the second as well as its spin-off feature films: Star Trek Generations, Star Trek: First Contact, Star Trek: Insurrection, and Star Trek: Nemesis. McFadden returned to the role in the third season of [[Star Trek: Picard]]. She also had cameo appearances in Star Trek: Prodigy, both as a holographic recreation and the real Crusher.

title: la_la_land
body: La La Land is a 2016 American musical romantic comedy-drama film written and directed by Damien Chazelle. It stars [[Ryan Gosling]] and [[Emma Stone]] as a struggling jazz pianist and an aspiring actress who meet and fall in love while pursuing their dreams in Los Angeles. The supporting cast includes John Legend, Rosemarie DeWitt, Finn Wittrock, and J. K. Simmons.

title: michael_cera
body:
Michael Austin Cera is a Canadian actor. Cera became known for portraying leading roles in a string of comedic films such as [[Superbad (movie)|]] (2007), Juno (2007), and [[scott pilgrim vs the world (movie)|Scott Pilgrim vs the World]] (2010), Nick & Norah's Infinite Playlist (2008), and Youth in Revolt (2009). He took supporting roles in both comedies and dramas including Confessions of a Dangerous Mind (2002), This Is the End (2013), Molly's Game (2017), Person to Person (2017), Gloria Bell (2019), [[barbie (live action)|Barbie]] (2023), and Dream Scenario (2023). He voiced [[Dick Grayson]]/ [[robin (dc)|Robin]] in [[The Lego Batman Movie]] (2017), Barry in [[Sausage Party]] (2016) and Hank in Paws of Fury: The Legend of Hank (2022).

Cera gained prominence portraying George Michael Bluth in the Fox sitcom Arrested Development from 2003 to 2006 and then again from 2013 to 2019. He took a leading role in the Hulu comedy series Life & Beth (2022–2024), and also voiced roles including reprising his roles as Scott Pilgrim in the Netflix series Scott Pilgrim Takes Off (2023), and Barry in the Amazon Prime Video series Sausage Party: Foodtopia (2024).

title: superbad_(movie)
body: Superbad is a 2007 American coming-of-age teen buddy comedy film directed by Greg Mottola, written by [[Seth Rogen]] and Evan Goldberg, and produced by Judd Apatow. It stars [[Jonah Hill]] and [[Michael Cera]] as Seth and Evan, two teenagers about to graduate from high school. Before graduating, the boys want to party and lose their virginity, but their plan proves harder than expected. [[Christopher Mintz-Plasse]] (in his film debut), Rogen, Bill Hader, Martha MacIsaac, and [[Emma Stone]] (in her film debut) provide supporting roles.

title: christopher_mintz-plasse
body: Christopher Charles Mintz-Plasse (/mɪnts ˈplɔːs/; born June 20, 1989) is an American actor. Primarily known for his work in comedy films, he has performed roles such as Fogell / McLovin in [[Superbad (movie)|]] (2007), Augie Farcques in Role Models (2008), and Chris D'Amico in [[Kick-Ass]] (2010) and its sequel Kick-Ass 2 (2013). He also played the role of "Evil" Ed Lee in the 2011 remake of Fright Night.

title: shiranui_flare_(old_design)
body:
The original default design of [[hololive]]'s [[Shiranui Flare]], consisting of two versions.

The first version consists of several pieces linked together including an inner top layer with cleavage and back cutouts, an outer corset, collar and capelet layer with shoulder and upper back cutouts, [[detached sleeves]] with elbow pit cutouts as well as a [[single thighhigh]] and pumps of contrasting colors.

The second version is basically the same, but with some of the fanservice aspects toned down. The inner top layer no longer has a cleavage cutout and is is strapless instead, and she now wears side-tie shorts instead of what is assumed to be side-tie panties. To accommodate the shorts, her single thighhigh is shorter. This version of the design was used for her original 3D model.

h4. Appearance

body:
[i][[Danganronpa V3: Killing Harmony]][/i] character.

The Ultimate Robot invented by [[Professor Iidabashi]]. He is a studious [[android]] learning what he can from the human students, but often feels prejudiced. While he was initially presented as a focal character in earlier promotional materials with [[Harukawa Maki]] and [[Momota Kaito]], the true protagonist was revealed later. Often seen with [[Oma Kokichi]] and [[Iruma Miu]].

He has [[short hair|short]] [[silver hair]] with  an [[ahoge]], and has [[blue eyes]]. As he is an android, his only clothes consist of [[power armor]]. His name is spelled as K1-B0 in the English localisation.

title: bamboo
body:
A tropical [[plant]] consisting of tall, green, tubular stems. It is technically a type of grass, but its woody tissue is as strong as timber, and the tallest species can grow to a height of nearly 100 feet (30 meters). Most species are native to Southeast Asia (around 64%), but the plant is also common in Latin America (around 33%). The rest are native mostly to Africa and Oceania, but North America does have three native species. 

Bamboo is used for various purposes, including cooking, construction, textiles, paper, furniture, and traditional medicine.

It is a dietary staple of the giant [[panda]], with which it is frequently depicted.

h4. See also 

* [[bamboo forest]] 
* [[bamboo broom]]

* [[kadomatsu]]

title: millenniumon
body:
A Composition Digimon. Millenniumon resembles a large feral beast, with four long, thin arms and large claws, and two large cannons on its back. It is said to be the fusion of a [[mugendramon|mechanical amalgam]] and an [[chimairamon|organic aberration]], and exudes immense power that transcends the limits of time and space.

In addition, it has two other forms: [[MoonMillenniumon]] and [[ZeedMillenniumon]].

title: mugendramon
body:
Type: Machine
Level: Ultimate
Attribute: Virus

A Machine [[Digimon]]. Mugendramon is a dinosaur-like amalgamation of parts from other Cyborg Digimon — [[Megadramon]]'s helmet and right claw, [[MetalTyranomon]]'s jaw and chest circuits, two of [[MetalMamemon]]'s Psycho Blasters, [[MetalGreymon]]'s left claw and chest plates, and [[Andromon]]'s shoulder pads. Its strongest Special Move is ∞ Cannon, for which it fires immensely strong energy waves from its twin cannons.

Mugendramon can be considered a mechanical counterpart to [[Chimairamon]], an organic Composite Digimon. Together, they can Jogress Evolve to become [[Millenniumon]].

Mugendramon is referred to as [b]Machinedramon[/b] in English material.

東方非想天則 ~ 超弩級ギニョルの謎を追え

title: hawkgirl
body: Hawkgirl is the name of several superheroines appearing in American comic books published by [[DC Comics]]. The original Hawkgirl, Shiera Sanders Hall, was created by writer Gardner Fox and artist Dennis Neville, and first appeared in Flash Comics #1 (January 1940). Shayera Hol was created by writer Gardner Fox and artist Joe Kubert, and first appeared in The Brave and the Bold #34 (March 1961). Kendra Saunders was created by writer David S. Goyer and artist Stephen Sadowski, and first appeared in JSA: Secret Files and Origins #1 (August 1999). One of DC's earliest super-heroines, Hawkgirl has appeared in many of the company's flagship team-up titles including Justice Society of America and [[Justice League|Justice League of America]].

body: A character from [[Cookie Run]]. He has [[short hair|short]] [[white hair]] that [[hair over eye|covers one eye]], and [[blue eyes]]. His default outfit includes a [[witch hat]] with a [[star print]] and a [[white scarf]]. He often carries a [[staff]]. h4. Official art * !asset #24237372 * !asset #24237364: [[wizard_cookie_(azure_flame_staff)|Azure Flame Staff]] h4. Trivia * He debuted on the first iteration, [[LINE Cookie Run]], during the 2nd Story update, May 28th 2014. h4. See also * [[List of Cookie Run characters]]
other_names: 魔法使いの味クッキー

title: flo_(animal_crossing)
body:
An [[Animal Crossing]] villager. 

She is a [[penguin]] with purple and white skin, along with [[black eyes]] that are [[half-closed eyes|half-closed]] by default.

h4. See also
* [[List of Animal Crossing characters]]

title: mint_(animal_crossing)
body:
An [[Animal Crossing]] villager. 

She is a [[squirrel]] with [[aqua fur|aqua]] or [[green fur]]; she has [[black eyes]] with [[lower eyelashes only|lower eyelashes]].

Her default outfit is a [[multicolored dress]] with [[short sleeves]].

h4. Official art
* !asset #24237232

h4. Trivia
* She debuted on Animal Crossing for Gamecube.
* Her Japanese name is Minto (ミント).
* Her name in other languages are: Amande, Menta, Marika, Mentulla, Xiaomin (小敏) and Minteu (민트)

h4. See also
* [[List of Animal Crossing characters]]

title: zoe_(animal_crossing)
body:
An [[Animal Crossing]] villager. 

She is an [[anteater]] with [[aqua fur|aqua]] and [[white fur]]. She has [[orange eyes]] with [[lower eyelashes only]].

Her default outfit is a [[pink shirt]] with a [[floral print]]. 

h4. Official art
* !asset #24236832

h4. Trivia
* She debuted in the first game, Doubutsu no Mori.
* Her original name, Bifuun (ビーフン), means 'rice noodles'. 
* Her name in other languages are Naricia, Cléo, Mifen (米粉) and Somyeon (소면).

h4. See also
* [[List of Animal Crossing characters]]
other_names: ビーフン(どうぶつの森)

title: olaf_(animal_crossing)
body:
An [[Animal Crossing]] villager. 

He is an [[anteater]] with either [[orange fur|orange]] or [[brown fur]], and [[short hair|short]] [[curly hair|curly]] [[brown hair]]. He has [[black eyes]] with [[lower eyelashes only]]. 

His default outfit includes a [[black jacket]] with a [[yellow trim]], along with a [[red necktie]].

h4. Official art
* !asset #24236993

h4. Trivia
* He debuted in New Leaf.
* His original Japanese name is Antonio (アントニオ).
* His name in other languages are Ettore, Blair, Andongni (安東尼) and Antonio (안토니오).#

h4. See also
* [[List of Animal Crossing characters]]

title: arvis_(fire_emblem)
body:
[b]Arvis[/b] is a character from [[Fire Emblem: Genealogy of the Holy War]]. He is the Duke of Velthomer, and a full-blooded descendant of Crusader [[Fjalar (Fire Emblem)|]], allowing him to use the sacred tome [[Valflame]].

Arvis serves as one of the main antagonists of the game. [spoiler]He is convinced to marry [[Deirdre (Fire Emblem)|]], both unaware that they share the same mother and are thus half-siblings. The result of their union are twin children, [[Julia (Fire Emblem)|]] and [[Julius (Fire Emblem)|]]. Arvis kills [[Sigurd (Fire Emblem)|]] and his companions in the Battle of Belhalla, slaughtering almost all of the first generation. Later, he ascends the throne as Emperor of Grannvale, although he effectively holds no power due to the Loptr Church controlling Grannvale behind his back. Arvis ultimately meets his end by the blade of Sigurd's son, [[Seliph (Fire Emblem)|]].[/spoiler]

title: fire_emblem:_genealogy_of_the_holy_war
body:
The fourth game in the [[Fire Emblem]] series, released in 1996 for the [[Super Famicom]].

The game is divided between two generations, with the First Generation featuring [[Sigurd (Fire Emblem)|]] and his exploits on the continent of Jugdral, as he unravels a conspiracy against the Kingdom of Grannvale. The Second Generation focuses on Sigurd's son, [[Seliph (Fire Emblem)|]], who leads a resistance against the now corrupt Grannvale Empire, orchestrated by the Cult of Loptous.

While obscure, it is generally considered one of the best Fire Emblem games ever made, due to its engaging story, interesting characters, and vast worldbuilding.

title: humvee
body:
The [b]High Mobility Multipurpose Wheeled Vehicle (HMMWV)[/b], commonly known as the [b]Humvee[/b], is a four-wheel-drive military automobile produced by the American company AM General since 1984.

It was the [[united states|U.S.]] armed forces replacement for the [[military jeep]], and is in turn being partly replaced by the Oshkosh L-ATV. 

Note that [[Hummer]] is the civilian version of the Humvee and has progressively become less and less similar to the military variant.

h4.See also

* "Wikipedia article":https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Humvee

title: mk19_grenade_launcher
body:
The Mk 19 (pronounced Mark 19) is an American 40 mm [b]automatic [[grenade launcher]][/b] that was first developed during the [[Vietnam War]]. Entered [[military]] service since 1968. It replaced the earlier hand-cranked "Mk 18":[https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Mk_18_Mod_0_grenade_launcher].

The Mk 19 is a belt-fed, blowback-operated, air-cooled, crew-served, fully-automatic [[weapon]] that is designed not to cook off. It fires 40 mm grenades at a cyclic rate of 325 to 375 rounds per minute, giving a practical rate of fire of 60 rounds per minute (rapid) and 40 rounds per minute (sustained). Though the Mk 19 has a flash suppressor, it serves only to save the eyesight of its operator, not concealing the weapon's position. For [[night]] operation, a picatinny rail quadrant sight can be added for [[thermal scope|thermal]] and [[night vision]] [[optical sight|optics]]. 

Due to its low recoil and comparatively light weight, the [[weapon]] has been adapted for use on many different platforms, including small attack [[boat]]s, [[aircraft]]s, fast attack vehicles such as the [[Humvee]], AAV and Stryker, [[military jeep]]s, and a large variety of naval mounts.

h4. See also
* [[AGS-30]] - The Russian "counterpart".
* [[List of weapons]]
* Wikipedia page: "Mk 19 grenade launcher":[https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Mk_19_grenade_launcher]

title: m151_(truck)
body: [b]Truck, Utility, ¼-Ton, 4×4, M151[/b] was the last generation of the traditional "[[military jeep|jeep]]" light utility vehicles fielded by the United States armed forces. It was developed by the Ford Motor Company under a 1951 contract to replace the U.S. Army's fleet of Willys M38 jeeps, which in turn were the successors to the original Bantam-based Willys MB and Ford GP jeeps of World War II. The M151 strongly resembles its predecessors, but is larger and based on a completely new platform. Visually, it is easily distinguished by its horizontally slotted front grille (since the classic vertical grille of the earlier jeeps was, by 1951, a trademarked aspect of the civilian Jeeps being sold by Willys). The M151 was replaced starting in 1983 by the [[humvee|HMMWV]], but a few examples are allegedly still used by some Special Forces units today.

title: tokusou_butai_jackkaru
body:
[b]Tokusou Butai Jackkaru[/b], also known in the west as [b]Jackal[/b] (and distributed under the title of [b]Top Gunner[/b]) is an overhead run-and-gun shooter [[video game]] by [[KONAMI]] released as an [[arcade]] in 1986. 

In the game the player must maneuver an armed [[military jeep]] in order to rescue prisoners of war (POWs) trapped in enemy territory.

Jackal was released for the [[Nintendo]] [[NES]] and [[Famicom]] [[game console]]s in 1988.

title: military_jeep
body:
A type of light utility vehicle, primarily used for military purposes or civilian offroading. The most prominent Jeep model used by the [[military vehicle|military]] was the Willys MB, since the World War II. The design was licensed for production to many marques around the world (in addition to unlicensed copycats), making it a ubiquitous design with many variants.

Jeeps are visually distinguishable by their seven-slot vertical grille flanked with two circular headlights.

This is a generic tag for Jeep-like utility vehicles regardless of specific model, manufacturer, or country of origin. For the modern American manufacturer, see [[Jeep (Company)]].

title: candy_kong
body:
A Kong introduced in [i][[Donkey Kong Country]][/i]. 

[[Donkey Kong]]'s rumored love interest and a good friend who always helps him out along with the other Kongs. She is sultry and alluring, always affectionate in manner and speech. 

In Donkey Kong Country she has a [[pink leotard]] and wears a [[large_bow|large]] [[pink bow]] on top of her head. In [[Donkey Kong 64]] she wears a [[pink shirt]] [[crop top]] with her name "Candy" [[clothes writing|written]] on it, [[pink shorts]] and is the only iteration to wear [[pink footwear|pink shoes]]. She also has [[purple eyeshadow]], [[pink nails|pink]] [[nail polish]], a [[necklace]] and carries a blue [[walkman]]. Her current standard look was introduced starting from [[DK: King of Swing]], having her retain much of the design introduced in Dk64, but now wears a [[pink camisole]] that retains her name written on it. Her eyeshadow is now more [[blue eyeshadow|blue]], she is [[barefoot]] again and loses her necklace and walkman. All iterations have [[medium hair|medium]] [[blonde hair]], [[large breasts]], pronounced [[pink lips|pink]] [[thick lips]] and most give her [[blue eyes]], though she had [[green eyes]] in the original DKC.

She is the tallest and most humanoid of the Kongs, standing completely upright and being the most proportioned like a human.

title: matsunaga_ryo
body:
An [i][[iDOLMASTER Cinderella Girls|iDOLM@STER Cinderella Girls]][/i] character in the Cool (Blue Diamond) category. Ryo is a horror movie and death metal fanatic, though she appreciates music genres like jazz and classical. She is a good friend of [[Shirasaka Koume]], as the two share many interests. While she enjoys horror, she tends to be bored by most horror films. That said, she isn't immune to fear like Koume and can be scared by ghosts.
She was a vocalist in a band, and in the anime, she was introduced as a member of [[Kimura Natsuki]] prospective band. However, she is a kind girl who cares about the other younger girls, like [[Sasaki Chie]] and [[Shirasaka Koume]], and how they feel. Her company often gets her into trouble, but she admits that she enjoys their antics as long as they end peacefully. 

Voiced by [[Chisuga Haruka]] [千菅 春香].

title: range_finder
body:
A device used to determine the distance between a 'target' and the observer. Range finders are usually seen in military applications, though they are also utilized in civilian use cases such as [[Golf]], [[Taking Picture|Photography]]. or forestry.

there are three predominant categories of range finder:
- [[Laser]]
     Usually the most compact, Laser Range Finders are often seen next to [[Sniper Rifle|snipers]], used to adjust lead for a shot.
- Stereoscopic
     A horizontal tube with apertures at either end and a pair of eye pieces near the center. Stereoscopic Range Finders make use of human stereoscopic vision to line up the images coming from either end to find an accurate distance to target.
- Coincidence
     Similar to the Stereoscopic Range Finder, albeit with only one eye piece, Coincidence Range Finders split the incoming images and overlay one top above the other's bottom. when the two images are adjusted to line up, an accurate range will be found.

In general, Stereoscopic and Coincidence Range Finders benefit from being wider and higher up, leading to them predominantly being seen high in the superstructure of warships up through [[World War II|WWII]] before being phased out in favor of [[radar]] range finders. Medium-to-large naval [[turret|turrets]] often featured one or more integrated range finders, such as are seen protruding from the sides of the 16-inch/50-caliber mark 7 gun turrets of the [[uss_iowa_(bb-61)|Iowa-class]].

title: feminization
body:
Also called "sissification", feminization is a type of fetish where the focus is on a man (particularly [[androgynous]] men) [[crossdressing]] and being groomed into behaving more feminine. Is often done as either an act of humiliation, as the result of hypnosis, or to establish dominance (especially in [[femdom]] relationships). Some examples may even include medical alterations, like those caused by hormone therapy or more supernatural means, though it needs to be clear the character was originally male.

This term also applies to [[tomboy|tomboyish]] girls being forced to act more conventionally feminine.

[b]Note:[/b] do not tag all content specifically focusing on a male at birth character [[crossdressing]] or with gender-questioning themes as feminization.

h4. See also
* [[Bimbofication]] - A similar concept of turning a character into a hyperfeminine version of themselves, but specifically made to be overly sexual and airheaded
* [[Genderswap (mtf)]] - Fiction often depicts sex changes far more complete than current medical science can produce. Both tags can overlap if it's clear without outside knowledge the character was previously male and an outside force caused them to become completely female.

title: fabius_bile
body:
Fabius Bile, also called the "Clone Lord," the "Primogenitor," the "Manflayer" and "the Spider," is a [[Chaos Space Marine]] [[apothecary_(warhammer 40k)|Apothecary]] and Chaos Lord, originally the Chief Apothecary of the [[Emperor's Children]] Legion, who has repeatedly attempted to use his extensive knowledge of cloning and genetic engineering to create superhuman beings under his control.

The goal of his quest for knowledge is to match and then exceed the [[Emperor of Mankind]]'s original scientific achievement in creating the [[primarch]]s and the transhuman [[Adeptus Astartes]], in the hope of creating a truly perfect human form.

title: century_egg_(food)
body:
Century eggs, also known as pidan, preserved eggs, hundred-year eggs, thousand-year eggs, thousand-year-old eggs, century-old eggs, millennium eggs, skin eggs, black eggs or old eggs are a traditional Asian dish featuring eggs that have been preserved in a curing mixture for several weeks to several months.

The outer egg white turns into a dark brown, translucent jelly, while the inner egg yolk becomes dark green and squishy.

title: rice_wine
body: "Sweet rice wine made by mixing steamed glutinous rice (sticky rice) with jiuqu (a type of special microbial yeast) for fermentation. The brewing process is simple, and it has a fragrant and mellow taste. It has a long history of over a thousand years in China."

title: awaria
body:
A short indie bullet hell/task manager game created by Polish developer [[vanripper]]. The full game is available for free on Steam, and can be comfortably beaten in about an hour and a half.

You take the roll of a tunnel runner. If the generators fail, it's your job to fix them. Check what's wrong, craft all the needed parts and deliver them. While avoiding safety violations and violent ghosts. 

The main character took the job for the main purpose of kissing ghosts.

title: gandalf
body:
Wizard character from [[the Lord of the Rings]] and other associated works in J.R.R. Tolkien's [[Tolkien's legendarium]].

[spoiler]Actually an embodied Maiar spirit, i.e. the LotR version of an angel, descended in human form.[/spoiler]

[[Ian McKellen]] portrayed Gandalf in The Lord of the Rings film series directed by Peter Jackson, after Sean Connery and [[Patrick Stewart]] both turned down the role.

title: aragorn
body: Aragorn (Sindarin: [ˈaraɡorn]) is a fictional character and a protagonist in J. R. R. Tolkien's [[The Lord of the Rings]]. Aragorn is a Ranger of the North, first introduced with the name Strider and later revealed to be the heir of Isildur, an ancient King of Arnor and Gondor. Aragorn is a confidant of the wizard [[Gandalf]] and plays a part in the quest to destroy the One Ring and defeat the Dark Lord [[Sauron]]. As a young man, Aragorn falls in love with the immortal elf [[Arwen]], as told in "The Tale of Aragorn and Arwen". Arwen's father, Elrond Half-elven, forbids them to marry unless Aragorn becomes King of both Arnor and Gondor.

title: uncongealed_tofu
body: Uncongealed tofu (豆腐脑) is a famous traditional dish in China. It is a highly nutritious food made from soybean protein, often sold in the morning, and is commonly combined with tofu flower and douhua. The taste varies by region; people in northern China tend to prefer savory flavors, while those in southern China favor sweet tastes. In some regions, such as Sichuan, there is also a preference for sour and spicy flavors.

title: portable_stove
body:
A [[stove|cooking stove]] that is designed to be portable and lightweight. They are used in [[camping]], [[picnic|picnicking]], and for other uses in remote locations where there is no other means of heating or cooking.  In low-end Japanese apartments their kitchens may be furnished with a portable 1-3 burner stove that hooks to the gas line.

Portable stoves are frequently used for cooking [[hotpot]]s.

title: mufasa
body: Mufasa is a major character in Disney's 1994 animated feature film [[The Lion King]]. He was a large, powerful [[lion]] who once served as king of the Pride Lands. Revered as a wise and noble leader, Mufasa dedicated his reign to upholding the “circle of life” and mentoring his only son, [[Simba]], to someday assume the throne. Mufasa’s younger brother, [[Scar (the lion king)|]], was secretly envious of the king and orchestrated a regicidal coup to steal the throne. Despite his death, Mufasa endures in the memories of his loved ones. His spirit manifests in clouds, stars, and sunlight, which has occasionally appeared to guide his descendants.

title: war_hammer
body:
A late [[medieval]] weapon of war originally intended for close combat action. It was designed to deliver heavy damage against well-armored opponents through sheer blunt force. Though some adapted it as a versatile [[polearm]] weapon instead by giving it a longer handle.

Real life war hammers are comparable in size with a regular carpentry [[hammer]], though with a longer handle and often a spike opposite the blunt head to pierce armor. This tag can also be applied to [[huge_weapon|huge]] fantasy [[weapon|weapons]] depicted simply as an oversized [[hammer]]/[[sledgehammer]].

Not to be confused with [[Warhammer 40k]].

h4. See also

* [[List of weapons]]

title: flail
body:
The flail is a medieval [[weapon]], made of (one or more) weight(s) attached to a handle with a hinge, [[rope]], or short [[chain]]. They originated from farming flails, which were used to thresh grain.

A rule of thumb, if the weapon has a chain over an arm's length (and more so over 1.5 arm's lengths), then the weapon is most likely a [[ball and chain (weapon)|]] instead.

title: huipai_architecture
body:
Hui-pai architecture is a type of building found in the Jiangnan region of China, characterized by white walls and black tiles.

The main city in the game Wuthering Waves, Luofu in honkai:_star_rail ,The chinese scene in Azur Promilia,
 and Chenyu Vale in Genshin Impact all feature huipai architecture as part of their game scenes.

title: alkaid_mcgrath_(eden)
body:
[[Lovebrush Chronicles]] character. [[Alkaid McGrath]]’s alternate self in the Eden. He is a mysterious gardener who insists on bringing the [[heroine (lovebrush chronicles)|]] to his home for a cup of tea. His true identity is the Master of Eden, master of the [[monster]]s known as “the Lost” and mastermind behind the battle royale. 

He wears either a [[white suit]], or a [[science fiction]]-esque outfit with [[puff and slash sleeves]] and [[white cloak]]. He’s associated with [[white rose]] and [[tea]].

title: clarence_clayden_(awakening)
body:
[[Lovebrush Chronicles]] character, Modern World’s [[Clarence Clayden]] in an alternate future shown in Awakening Chapter. He is Clarence-04D-4711, a Type 04-D [[Android]], who is awakened from a hibernation chamber a hundred year after Earth’s fall with his memory hazy of who he really is.

He has [[short hair]] and wears a [[black jacket]] and a [[scouter]].

title: clarence_clayden_(spirit_world)
body:
[[Lovebrush Chronicles]] character, [[Clarence Clayden]]’s alternate self in Spirit World. Lord of the Wind, formerly Lord of the Sea, and the first Spirit Lord to ever ascend. Being the one the Caelum Tower originated from, he knows all about its secrets, but prefers to remain silent and uninvolved in the grand scheme after having witnessed three circles of apocalypse.

He has [[long hair]] in a [[single braid]] and wears a [[white robe]], [[black cape]], [[black gloves]], [[gold necklace]], [[gold earrings]], and a [[monocle]]. There’re [[black horns]] on one side of his head. His animal form is a [[oversized animal|giant]] [[winged animal|feathered]] [[white snake]] inspired by Quetzalcoatls. His symbol is the [[infinity symbol]] or the [[mobius strip]].

title: clarence_clayden_(eden)
body:
[[Lovebrush Chronicles]] character, [[Clarence Clayden]]’s alternate self in Eden. He is a NEOS with augmented senses, serving as a freelance mercenary and hailed as “the strongest NEOS in the desert”. He was the first NEOS the [[heroine (lovebrush chronicles)|]] met who guided her to Eden and also entered it later for what he called a "sightseeing trip", but isn’t interested in joining the battle royale himself. 

He has [[short hair]] and notably wears a [[white shirt]], [[bulletproof vest]], dark [[blue coat]], and a pair of [[orange-tinted eyewear]]. He primarily wields a [[sniper rifle]] in battle alongside various [[gun]]s, and rides a [[motorcycle]]. His motif is the [[falcon]].

He is distinguished by his [[blue cloak]] and [[swept bangs]]. His [[aged down|younger]] depiction shows him in a [[sailor shirt]] and [[white shorts]].
